Q35:
Personally I would think questions like "rate level of pain out of 10" and "does headache lead to loss of vision" could lead to very subjective answers that vary from person to person.
The level of pain could be skewed by the person's pain tolerance level, and the "loss of vision" could be interpreted as either complete loss of vision or just slight blurriness. 
If the result of the diagnosis is based on such subjective answers, then I might doubt the accuracy of the result. But if I were to have such symptoms then I would trust the app's advice and see a GP immediately.

So overall I think the app works for it's intended purpose.
